      "writtenOn": "2020-02-12T01:40:06Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Are you inferring that we should panic if either `id` or any field in `builder` is missing? \n\nI would definitely agree that we should panic when id is missing since that seems to be an invalid state. However, I\u0027m think not requesting for builder is a legit use case (May be user are just interested in id and status). \n\n\nMy idea would be we can print following the order of `project-\u003ebucket-\u003ebuilder-\u003enumber`. If any field on the chain is missing, we\u0027ll stop at that point. That means if only `project` and `builder` are present but `bucket` is missing, we will only print `project`. What do you think?",
